<s> Just to let you know that I've coded some new tools recently that some of you might find useful to clean up a specification: - the W3C spell checker: (works for HTTP-protected resource) A simple spell checker using aspell in the back-end; - the W3C stylistic checker: (doesn't work for HTTP-protected resource, but could easily do so if necessary and requested) Use GNU diction in the back-end and a home-grown set of rules to match some of the advices given by the W3C Manual of style.  </s>
